Print method for <multi_epidist> class

Source: R/print.R
print.multi_epidist.Rd

Print method for <multi_epidist> class

Usage

# S3 method for multi_epidist
print(x, ..., n = NULL)

Arguments

x

A <multi_epidist> object.

...

dots Extra arguments to be passed to the method.

n

A numeric specifying how many <epidist> objects to print. This argument is passed to head() for list printing. Default is NULL and the number of elements to print is controlled by package options().

Value

Invisibly returns a <multi_epidist>. Called for side-effects.

Examples

# entire database
db <- epidist_db()
